1 driving for the St. Martin Parish School Board, touching the lives of countless students with
2 his kindness, dedication, and care, and he also owned and operated Nelson's Lawnmower
3 Repair Shop and Service Station, continuing to serve the people of his beloved community;
4 and
5 WHEREAS, Thomas was leader, trusted friend, and pillar of the community, where
6 he was known for his kind heart and generous spirit, creating a lasting impact for generations
7 to come; and
8 WHEREAS, he is survived by his wife of sixty-seven years, Ursula St. Andre'
9 Nelson; daughters, Francisca Taylor (Carrol), Lisa Nelson, Vonda LeBlanc, and Sherri Sigue
10 (Lurry); brothers, Lloyd Nelson, John Nelson, and McKinley Nelson (Nam); and a host of
11 grandchildren and great-grandchildren; and
12 WHEREAS, Louis "Thomas" Nelson lived his life with dignity and humility, always
13 placing family, faith, and service above all else, and his legacy will live on in the countless
14 lives he touched with his wisdom and kindness as well as in the strong and vibrant
15 community he helped build.
16 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
17 does hereby express sincere and heartfelt condolences to the family of Louis "Thomas"
18 Nelson upon his passing and does hereby commend his dedication to public service and his
19 many accomplishments.
20 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
21 family of Louis "Thomas" Nelson.
